# tests

these tests verify if the latest mvm build has been successful by making sure it
still works as intended. all of these tests are run and their stdout is compared
again an expected output .txt of the same name by the test script.

[hello world.magneta]
  writes "Hello, World!"

[registers.magenta]
  pops data into all 8 registers, and depops all 8 registers in reverse

[math.magenta]
  tests the addition and subtraction commands from 1 through 8 byte byte widths
[logic.magenta]
  tests the greater and equal logic commands

[jmp.magenta]
  print 0-255 on screen then exit
[jmpsub.magenta]
  writes "Hello, Subroutines!", using subroutines

[memory.magenta]
  tests reading/writing blocks from different points in memory

[iobus memory.magenta]
  test allocating additional memory via. the io bus
[iobus stdio.magenta]
  test reading from stdin and writing to stdout and stderr
[iobus generic file.magenta]
  test reading and writing from a file

[strings.magenta]
  test conversion commands, reversing command, and the memory string read/write
  commands.
